<h2 class="ps-0 ms-0 pt-2 standard-green">Common issues</h2>
<h3>I don't see any menu or content, why?</h3>
<p>
    Some accesses are granted according to your Wondows account, the one you use to log into tools.
    To this account, we create groups, which will grant you access or not to a tool or a specific part of a tool.
    Please make a request to your superior, copy to IT, if you need to access a tool/a part of a tool.
</p>
<h3>I can't access from my mobile phone, when I'm outside the office</h3>
<p>
    Not all tools are set to be accessible from outside, this needs some technical securities to develop for each of them.
    From your professional computer, you can access tools from outside if VPN (Virtual Private Network) is launched and set up.
    Please make a request to your superior, copy to IT, if you need to access a tool from outside.
</p>

<h2 class="ps-0 ms-0 pt-2 standard-green">Common debug mode</h2>
<figure class="col-5 d-inline-block m-0 p-0">
    <img src="/img/help/help_debug_mode.png"/>
    <figcaption>Debug mode</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>The <strong>Debug Mode</strong> is a mode in which errors are displayed.
    This mode is useful to help developer to see detailed error messages.</p>
<p>
    When Debug Mode is set, the GMD logo is replaced by a triangled bug logo, 
    the top menu is yellow-backgrounded 
    and a statistic bar is displayed at the bottom.
</p>

<h2 class="ps-0 ms-0 pt-2 standard-green">Common table sorting and filtering</h2>
<p>Most tables can be sorted and filtered, 
    excepted ones with complex structures (multi-line rows).
    In such case, column headers don't display sort arrows.</p>
<p><strong>Sort</strong> is enabled on clicking the two arrows on the right of a column.</p>
<figure class="col-3 d-inline-block m-0 p-0">
    <img src="/img/help/help_column_sort.png" style="height:150px;"/>
    <figcaption>Unsorted column</figcaption>
</figure>
<figure class="col-3 d-inline-block m-0 p-0">
    <img src="/img/help/help_column_sort_up.png" style="height:150px;"/>
    <figcaption>Sorted column</figcaption>
</figure>
<figure class="col-3 d-inline-block m-0 p-0">
    <img src="/img/help/help_column_sort_down.png" style="height:150px;"/>
    <figcaption>Reverse sorted column</figcaption>
</figure>
<p><strong>Filter</strong> is enabled on clicking the title of the column. The filter can be cancelled by typing the <strong>Escape</strong> key on focus.</p>
<figure class="col-4 d-inline-block m-0 p-0">
    <img src="/img/help/help_column_filter_1.png" style="height:250px;"/>
    <figcaption>Click on the column title</figcaption>
</figure>
<figure class="col-4 d-inline-block m-0 p-0">
    <img src="/img/help/help_column_filter_2.png" style="height:250px;"/>
    <figcaption>Applied filter</figcaption>
</figure>

<h2 class="ps-0 ms-0 pt-2 standard-green">Common keyboard shortcuts</h2>
<p>The shortcuts only works on <em>Windows computers</em>, 
    not on Apple computers nor Android/iOS smartphones/tablets. 
    Compatible browsers are tagged before each shortcut.</p>
<p>Note: The <em>Shift</em> key is the one without a lockup 
    <i class="fas fa-lock"></i> (second line from the bottom). 
    The one with the lockup is called the <em>Caps</em> key, 
    for <em>Capital letters</em> (upper case) and is not detected 
    as <em>Shift</em> key in shortcuts.</p>
<table class="table border">
    <thead class="standard-bg-grey standard-white">
        <tr>
            <th colspan="2" rowspan="2">Shortcut</th>
            <th colspan="5" rowspan="2">Description</th>
            <th colspan="3" class="text-center"><img src="/img/windows.png" style="height:16px;"/></th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <th class="text-center"><img src="/img/edgenew.png" style="height:16px;"/></th>
            <th class="text-center"><img src="/img/firefox.png" style="height:16px;"/></th>
            <th class="text-center"><img src="/img/chrome.png" style="height:16px;"/></th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td colspan="2" class="fw-bold">Ctrl+Alt+P</td>
            <td  colspan="5" >Takes a screen capture of the current screen, 
                removing top menu.</td>
            <td class="text-center">X</td>
            <td class="text-center">X</td>
            <td class="text-center">X</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td colspan="2" class="fw-bold">Ctrl+Alt+Shift+P</td>
            <td  colspan="5" >Allows you to take a screen capture 
